               <msContents>
                  <msItem xml:id="ms_i1">
                     <rubric>Nomina sacra; two initial lines on the incipit page of Texts I, II, III, IV; two initial lines of some sections of Text I; two pairs of initial lines of section I-3 alternating with black lines; two initial lines of section I-2; elements of the punctuation signs; elements of Ethiopic numerals; quire marks.&#xD;
Some terms and words, like ḥatäta (e.g. fols. 1rv, 3rv, 4rv), täśäṭwo (e.g. fols. 1-4), ʾǝm-mäṣḥaf (fol. 13v), tǝrgwame (fol. 13v), zǝntu wǝʾǝtu (fol. 21r), kǝfǝl qädamawi (fol. 11r), täfṣametä mǝnbab (fol. 31r).</rubric>
                     <incipit>
                        <foreign xml:lang="en"/>
                     </incipit>
                     <explicit>
                        <foreign xml:lang="en"/>
                     </explicit>
                     <note/>
                  </msItem>
                  <!--The data in the items below refers to other items. please remove this items and move the information to the appropriate place.-->
                  <msItem xml:id="ms_i2">
                     <note>Text IV (unidentified) is preceded by two notes on fol. 128v:</note>
                     <note>1) Note on symbolic interpretation of the covenant made between Abraham and Abimelech:</note>
                     <note/>
                     <note>ወነሥአ: አብርሃም: አልህምተ: ወወሀቦሙ: ወአቀመ: ፸ አባግዓ: ባሕቲቶን: … “Abraham took cows and gave them (to Abimelech). And he set seventy lambs by themselves …” (s. Gen. 21:27-31)</note>
                     <note/>
                     <note>2) Note on the purity and perpetual virginity of Mary:</note>
                     <note/>
                     <note>አእሚሮ: ከሀሌ: ኵሉ: ከመ: ይለብስ: ሥጋ: እጓለ: እመሕያው: ፈጠራ: ለቅድስት: ድንግል: ውስተ: ከርሠ: እማ: … “Knowing that He assumes the body of mankind, the Omnipotent created the Holy Virgin in the womb of her mother …”</note>
                  </msItem>
               </msContents>
