                        <item xml:id="a1">
                           <locus target="#132v">Fol. 132v</locus>: Note on types and qualities of precious stones.<q xml:lang="gez">Fol. 132v: እጽሕፍ: ነገረ: አዕናቍ: ቀይሐን: ወኅብረ: ደም: ወጸዓዳን: ወሐመልሚላን: ወኅብረ: ስሞሙሂ: ጳዝዮን: … </q>
                           <q xml:lang="en">Fol. 132v: I write the account of precious stones: red ones, those like blood, white ones, green ones, and there common name is Ṗazǝyon …</q>
                           The note is written in the same hand as Additio 2.
                        </item>
                        <item xml:id="a2">
                           <locus target="#132v">Fol. 132v</locus>: Note on symbolic interpretation of Biblical peoples as different animals. <q xml:lang="gez">Fol. 132v: ምሳሌ: አሕዛብ: አናብስት: ባቢሎን: አናምርት: ሚዶን: ድብ: ፋርስ: አዝዕብት: ግብጽ: አክልብት: ኢሎፍሊ: … </q>
                           <q xml:lang="en">Fol. 132v: Symbolic interpretation of peoples: Babylon (is like) Lion, <i>Midon </i>(is like) tigers, Persia (is like) bear, Egypt (is like) hyenas, Philistines (<i>ʾIlofli</i>) (are like) dogs …  </q>
                           The note is written in the same hand as Additio 1.
                        </item>
